Seven Congolese women were arrested by Siaya police officers on Saturday on suspicion of child trafficking.The women were found keeping 12 children aged between one month and 10 years at Sinaga area within Gem sub-county.Area county commissioner Josephine Onunga said the women were found to be in the country illegally.She said they were found in a house owned by a woman who runs a hotel at Sinaga market."We are also investigating if the host is part of the suspected child trafficking syndicate," Onunga said.The police were alerted by suspicious members of the public as the women could neither speak English nor Kiswahili.The administrator revealed that the seven women plus the children are currently being held at Yala Police station.Onunga said that the lot does not have any documentation that can reveal their identity and will be taken to court on Monday.